<article id="post-2888" class="post-2888 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-rants tag-elections tag-politics">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2011/03/dear-canada-grow-a-backbone/" rel="bookmark">Dear Canada, grow a backbone!</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Well, Canada, we&#8217;re in another pickle. The on-going &#8220;me, too!&#8221; power struggle that has dogged us for <strong>five years</strong> is now going into Round 3, thanks to a non-confidence (read: get enough people to whine the ruling party out of power) vote. In just over a month, we&#8217;re back at the polls, likely to do what we did last time, and the time before that: <strong>Make no decision whatsoever</strong>.<br />
I dunno what it is, but we Canadians seem to really love to not rock the boat. We don&#8217;t want heavy-handed politics, but we also want our cake and eat it, too. We want our health care, dammit, but <strong>we don&#8217;t want to pay for it</strong>. We want to leave our lights on 24/7, but please don&#8217;t raise our energy bills. And above all, we still want to be the &#8220;Nice&#8221; people in North America.<br />
Let&#8217;s face it, folks, <strong>we&#8217;re a bunch of pansies</strong>.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2011/03/dear-canada-grow-a-backbone/#more-2888" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Dear Canada, grow a backbone!&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2011/03/dear-canada-grow-a-backbone/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2011-03-28T16:03:30-06:00">28 March 2011</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/rants/" rel="category tag">Rants</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/elections/" rel="tag">elections</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/politics/" rel="tag">politics</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2011/03/dear-canada-grow-a-backbone/#comments">3 Comments<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Dear Canada, grow a backbone!</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
